                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Nuke panel
                            
	Melbourne, June 9 (PTI): Australia today announced the setting up of a global body for nuclear disarmament and ruled out sale of uranium to India until it signs the nuclear non-proliferation treaty.         
	Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd announced creation of the nuclear non-proliferations and disarmament commission during his visit to Japan, hoping to bring in like-minded countries.                                                                                                                                                                          
